x.de/bake_kw.htm DL8WX's Worldwide HF Beacon List] \n* HFLink{{Snd}} [http://hflink.com/5mhz 5&nbsp;MHz Channel ALE Frequencies]\n* [http://raynet-hf.net/about-us/scheduled-nets/ RAYNET (UK Amateur Radio Emergency Communications) HF Team Schedule]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:60-Meter Band}}\n[[Category:Amateur radio bands]]\n", "name_user": "Paul Gaskell", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCountries with band allocations", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/60-meter_band"}
{"title_page": "Victor Magtanggol", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Victor Magtanggol\n| image = Victor Magtanggol title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| show_name_2 = Heart of Courage<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmaworldwide.tv/programs/1/series/2/fantasy-and-action-adventure/1/show/503/heart-of-courage/|title=Heart of Courage |accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| genre = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Action (genre)|Action]]\n* [[Fantasy]]}}\n| creator = Jules Katanyag\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* Denoy Navarro-Punio\n* Glaiza Ramirez\n* Jules Katanyag\n* John Kenneth de Leon}}\n| director = [[Dominic Zapata]]\n| creative_director = [[Roy C. Iglesias|Roy Iglesias]]\n| starring = [[Alden Richards]]\n| theme_music_composer = [[Ex Battalion]]\n| opentheme = \"Superhero Mo\" by Ex Battalion feat. Alden Richards\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| num_episodes = 80\n| list_episodes = List of Victor Magtanggol episodes\n| executive_producer = Mona Coles-Mayuga\n| location = Philippines\n| editor = {{plain list|\n* Cesar Colina\n* Jennalyn Sablaya\n* Debbie Robete\n* Roslainy Barody\n* Tricia Senir}}\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime = 32-45 minutes\n| company = GMA Entertainment Group\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired = {{start date|2018|7|30}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2018|11|16}}\n| website = http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/victor_magtanggol\n}}\n\n'''''Victor Magtanggol''''' (International title: ''Heart of Courage'') is a 2018 [[Philippine television drama]] action-fantasy series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. The series is inspired by [[Norse mythology]]. Directed by [[Dominic Zapata]], it stars [[Alden Richards]] in the title role. It premiered on July 30, 2018, on the network's Telebabad line up, replacing ''[[The Cure (TV series)|The Cure]]''. The series concluded on November 16, 2018 with a total of 80 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[Cain at Abel]]'' in its timeslot.\n\nOriginally titled as ''Mitho'', it marked as the comeback show of [[Coney Reyes]] to the network after four years.<ref name=\"Alden\">{{cite web|URL=http://balita.net.ph/2018/03/06/action-fantasy-series-nina-alden-at-janine-may-taping-sa-ibang-bansa/ |title=Action-fantasy series nina Alden at Janine, may taping sa ibang bansa|trans-title=There is filming overseas for Alden and Janine's action-fantasy series |author=Angelli Catan |date=March 6, 2018 |accessdate=April 2, 2018|language=Filipino}}</ref> The series is streaming online on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGRhcC_vtOrbRN0Vm5JxgSSnXZ1BDROYM |title=Victor Magtanggol Full Episodes |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nMany gods, including [[Thor]], will not survive the [[Ragnar\u00f6k]]. Before Thor's death, he orders his son [[M\u00f3\u00f0i and Magni|Magni]] to hide his weapon, the hammer [[Mj\u00f6lnir]], until there is someone right to inherit it. Magni goes to the world of mortals to wait for the new taker of Mj\u00f6lnir. There he meets Victor Magtanggol, the one who must eventually learn to use Mj\u00f6lnir to protect the world and his loved ones from M\u00f3\u00f0i, Thor's son and Magni's brother, who is upset for not inheriting Mj\u00f6lnir, and [[Loki]] who plans to spread chaos in the mortal world.<ref name=victorabout>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/victor_magtanggol/about/ |title=Victor Magtanggol |accessdate=July 16, 2018 |language=Filipino}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Alden Richards at the OMG Awards.jpg\n|caption1 = Alden Richards portrays Victor Magtanggol.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Janine Gutierrez 2016.png\n|caption2 = Janine Gutierrez portrays Gwen Regalado.\n|width2 = 150\n|image3 = John Estrada.jpg\n|caption3 = John Estrada portrays Loki.\n|width3 = 150\n|image4 = Ortaleza.png\n|caption4 = Chynna Ortaleza portrays Lynette Magtanggol-Domingo.\n|width4 = 150\n|image5 = Benjie Paras NBA Asia Challenge 2010.jpg\n|caption5 = Benjie Paras portrays Erwin Bravo.\n|width5 = 150\n}}\n\n<!--Official cast billing from GMA Network-->\n;Lead cast\n* [[Alden Richards]] as Victor \"Hammerman\" Magtanggol<ref name=pepvictor>{{cite web|author1=PEP Troika |title=Victor Magtanggol ni Alden Richards, handa nang banggain ang Probinsyano ni Coco Martin|url=https://www.pep.ph/pepalerts/pep-troika/22315/victor-magtanggol-ni-alden-richards-handa-nang-banggain-ang-probinsyano-ni-coco-martin |accessdate=July 23, 2018 |work=PEP |publisher=Philippine Entertainment Portal, Inc. |date=July 23, 2018 |language=Tagalog, English}}</ref>\n* [[Coney Reyes]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Vivienne Delos Santos-Magtanggol\n* [[Eric Quizon]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Hector Regalado\n* [[Andrea Torres]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as [[Sif]] / Ms. S\n* [[Janine Gutierrez]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Gwen Regalado-Corona\n* [[Pancho Magno]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as [[M\u00f3\u00f0i and Magni|M\u00f3\u00f0i]]\n* [[John Estrada]]<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|author=Junardo |title=Sino kaya kina Maine, Jasmine at Janine ang itatambal kay Alden sa Victor Magtanggol?|trans-title=Who among Maine, Jasmine, and Janine will be paired up with Alden in Victor Magtanggol?|url=https://www.pressreader.com/philippines/bandera-visayas/20180527/281779924796089 |website=PressReader |publisher=Bandera Visayas |accessdate=July 5, 2018 |language=Filipino}}</ref> as [[Loki]] / Dr. Mikolai\n\n;Supporting cast\n* [[Al Tantay]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Tomas Magtanggol\n* [[Freddie Webb]]<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as Renato Regalado\n* [[Chynna Ortaleza]]<ref name=\"cast2\">{{cite web|URL=https://twitter.com/noivcalderon/status/1016300750660440065?|title=The cast of \u2018Victor Magtanggol\u2019 |author=Calderon, Noiv |accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref> as Lynette Magtanggol-Domingo / [[Hel (being)|Hel]]\n* [[Maritoni Fernandez]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Alice Espiritu-Regalado\n* [[Dion Ignacio]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Percival \"Perci\" Domingo\n* [[Kristofer Martin]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Lance E. Regalado / [[Fenrir]]\n* Miguel Faustmann<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as [[M\u00f3\u00f0i and Magni|Magni]] / Magnus\n* [[Yuan Francisco]]<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://tnt.abante.com.ph/yuan-francisco-sidekick-ni-alden-richards-sa-victor-magtanggol/ |title=Yuan Francisco, sidekick ni Alden Richards sa \u2018Victor Magtanggol\u2019 |author=Ma\u00f1ago, Lito |accessdate=July 13, 2018}}</ref> as Carmelo \"Meloy\" M. Domingo\n* Lindsay De Vera<ref name=\"Cast\"/> as Anne Magtanggol\n* Reese Tuazon<ref name=\"Cast\">{{cite web |title=Cast of Victor Magtanggol |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/victor_magtanggol/cast/}}</ref> as Honelyn De Mesa\n* [[Benjie Paras]]<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as Erwin Bravo\n* [[Lucho Ayala]]<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as Timothy Ferdinand \"Tim\" Corona\n* King Badger<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as Mario Magtanggol\n* Flow-G<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as Luigi Magtanggol\n\n;Guest cast\n* [[Conan Stevens]]<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as [[Thor]]\n* Matthias Rhoads as James\n* [[Diana Zubiri]] as [[Freyja|Freya]]\n* [[Fabio Ide]]<ref name=\"cast2\"/> as [[Baldr|Baldur]]\n* [[Natalia Moon]] as [[Frigg]]\n* [[Sheena Halili]]<ref name=\"cast3\">{{cite web|URL=https://www.bulgaronline.com/single-post/2018/07/10/ALDEN-AT-CO-STAR-HULI-SA-AKTO-SA-TENT |title=Nagbibihis na raw nang maabutan, Maine... Alden At Co-star, Huli Sa Akto Sa Tent |date=July 10, 2018 |author=Miralles, Nitz |accessdate=August 16, 2018}}</ref> as Janice\n*Luri Vincent Nalus<ref name=\"cast3\"/> as Dennis\n* Michelle Dee<ref name=\"cast3\"/> as Gwen's boss\n* [[Chariz Solomon]] as Cynthia\n* [[John Feir]] as a construction worker\n* [[Pekto]] as Ringgo\n* [[Rob Moya]] as a construction worker\n* [[Kevin Santos]] as James\n* [[Carlos Agassi]] as Arvin\n* [[Sophie Albert]] as [[Edda]]\n* [[Glaiza de Castro]] as Ena<ref name=\"cast4\">{{cite web|URL=https://m.facebook.com/SolidKapusoLU/photos/a.526309037420254/2067978339919975/? |title=Abangan ang mga Sang'gre ng Encantadia sa 'Victor Magtanggol' soon. |accessdate=September 14, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Kylie Padilla]] as Ami<ref name=\"cast4\"/>\n* [[Gabbi Garcia]] as Lena<ref name=\"cast4\"/>\n* [[Sanya Lopez]] as Aya<ref name=\"cast4\"/>\n* [[Pen Medina]] as Alcala\n* Janice Hung as [[Gunnlod]]\n* Ian Ignacio as [[Thrym]]\n* Tonio Quiazon as a gun smuggler\n* Noel Urbano as the voice of [[Nidhogg]] and [[Ratatoskr]]\n\n==Production==\n[[GMA Network (company)|GMA Network]] tasked writers to come up for a television series based on [[Norse mythology]].<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.msn.com/en-ph/news/other/konsepto-at-istorya-ng-victor-magtanggol-inspired-ng-norse-mythology/vi-AAzYdE8 |title=Konsepto at istorya ng 'Victor Magtanggol,' inspired ng Norse mythology |trans-title=Concept and story in 'Victor Magtanggol' inspired from Norse mythology|accessdate=July 13, 2018|language=Filipino}}</ref> Jules Katanyag, concept creator of ''Victor Magtanggol'' described what he and other writers came up as \"best reflects the Filipino condition,\" which is that of uncertainty.<ref name=notthor>{{cite web|title=\u2018Victor Magtanggol\u2019 based on Norse mythology, not Marvel\u2019s Thor, says creator |url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/282799/victor-magtanggol-based-norse-mythology-not-marvels-thor-says-creator |accessdate=July 14, 2018 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=July 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe show is set in present-day Philippines, after several [[Norse deities]] including Thor died following Ragnar\u00f6k, a series of catastrophic events in the [[Norse Mythology]].<ref name=notthor/> Part of the series was also shot outside of the Philippines.<ref name=\"Alden\"/>\n\nThe [[theme song]] \"Superhero Mo,\" is a collaboration between Alden Richards and hip-hop group, [[Ex Battalion]]. The later composed the song. A [[lyric video]] for the song was released by [[GMA Music]] on May 28, 2018.<ref name=\"collab\">{{cite web|author=Padayhag, Michelle Joy |title=Alden Richards collaborates with Ex Batallion for \u2018Victor Magtanggol\u2019 theme song |url=http://cebudailynews.inquirer.net/177390/alden-richards-collaborates-ex-batallion-victor-magtanggol-theme-song |accessdate=July 18, 2018 |work=Cebu Daily News |publisher=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=May 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Ratings==\nAccording to [[AGB Nielsen Philippines]]' Nationwide Urban Television Audience Measurement People in Television Homes, the pilot episode of ''Victor Magtanggol'' earned a 12.4% rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/FagutaoJimmuel/status/1024226074438164482?|title=Jeraska Fagutao 12 on Twitter: \"Victor Magtanggol managed to acquire one of the highest pilot episodes of GMA Telebabad to date and it is expected to topple Ang Probinsyano soon or maybe on {{sic|it's|nolink=y}} brilliant pilot week.\" |date=July 31, 2018 |accessdate=May 15, 2019}}</ref> While the final episode scored an 11.1% rating.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GoodThing193/status/1064388085083910144? |title=Yera Calma on Twitter: \"AGB Nielsen NUTAM People ratings November 16, 2018 (Friday )\" |date=November 19, 2018 |accessdate=May 15, 2019}}</ref> The series got its highest rating on August 1, 2018 with a 12.7% rating.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Showbiz_Polls/status/1024512227259211776?|title=Entertainment Uptake on Twitter |date=August 1, 2018 |accessdate=August 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Awards\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[33rd PMPC Star Awards for Television]]\n| Best Drama Actor\n| Alden Richards\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/146277/33rd-star-awards-for-television-names-tv-queens-pmpc-bares-nominees |title=33rd Star Awards for Television names TV Queens; PMPC bares nominees |work=Pep.ph |language=en |author=Dimaculangan, Jocelyn |date=September 22, 2019 |accessdate=September 23, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official site|http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/victor_magtanggol}}\n* {{IMDB title|8760072}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network drama series]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:2018 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2018 Philippine television series endings]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Fantaserye and telefantasya]]\n[[Category:Superhero television programs]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series based on Norse mythology]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Victor Magtanggol\n| image = Victor Magtanggol title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| show_name_2 = Heart of Courage<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmaworldwide.tv/programs/1/series/2/fantasy-and-action-adventure/1/show/503/heart-of-courage/|title=Heart of Courage |accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| genre = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Action (genre)|Action]]\n* [[Fantasy]]}}\n| creator = Jules Katanyag\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* Denoy Navarro-Punio\n* Glaiza Ramirez\n* Jules Katanyag\n* John Kenneth de Leon}}\n| director = [[Dominic Zapata]]\n| creative_director = [[Roy C. Iglesias|Roy Iglesias]]\n| starring = [[Alden Richards]]\n| theme_music_composer = [[Ex Battalion]]\n| opentheme = \"Superhero Mo\" by Ex Battalion feat. Alden Richards\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| num_episodes = 80\n| list_episodes = List of Victor Magtanggol episodes\n| executive_producer = Mona Coles-Mayuga\n| location = Philippines\n| editor = {{plain list|\n* Cesar Colina\n* Jennal