{"title_page": "List of post-disco artists and songs", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\nThe term '''[[post-disco]]''' is a referral to the early to late 1980s era movement of [[disco]] music into more stripped-down [[Electronic music|electronic]] [[funk]] influenced sounds; post-disco was also predecessor to [[house music]].\n\nThis chronological list contains examples of artists, songs and albums described as [[post-disco]], as well as its subgenre, [[Boogie (genre)|boogie]].\n{|border=\"0\" align=\"center\" class=\"toccolours\"\n!{{MediaWiki:Toc}}\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|'''[[#Artists|Some artists]]''': [[#A|A]] [[#B|B]] [[#C|C]] [[#D|D]] [[#E|E]] [[#F|F]] [[#G|G]] [[#I|I]] [[#J|J]] [[#K|K]] [[#L|L]] [[#M|M]] [[#N|N]] [[#O|O]] [[#P|P]] [[#R|R]] [[#S|S]] [[#U|U]] [[#W|W]] [[#Y|Y]] [[#Z|Z]]<br>'''[[#Songs|Some songs]]''': [[#1970s|1970s]] \u2022 [[#1980s|1980s]] \u2022 [[#2000s and 2010s|2000s and 2010s]]<br>'''[[#Albums|Some albums]]'''\n__NOTOC__\n|}\n\n==Songs==\n\n===1970s===\n{|align=\"center\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"3\" border=\"0\" style=\"font-size: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;\" width=\"60%\"\n|-bgcolor=\"silver\"\n!Year||Artist||Origin||Song||Label\n|-style=\"background: #c0ffff; color: black\"\n|rowspan=\"4\" height=15|'''[[1979 in music|1979]]'''|| [[Can (band)|Can]] || {{flagicon|DE}} || \"Aspectacle\"{{sfn|Brackett|Hoard|2004|p=135|ps=: the tense, jagged postdisco groove \"Aspectacle\"}} || ''[[Harvest Records|Harvest]]'' / ''[[Lightning Records|Lightning]]''\n|-\n|[[Gina X Performance|Gina X]] || {{flagicon|DE}} || \"No G.D.M.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|first= James |last= Friedman |title= Masked Masters |magazine= [[The Fader]] |issue= 14 |id= Fall 2002 |page= 38 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=Y2-fAAAAMAAJ&q=%22post+disco%22}}</ref> || ''[[Crystal Records|Crystal]]'' / ''[[EMI]]''\n|-\n|[[Shalamar]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[The Second Time Around (Shalamar song)|The Second Time Around]]\"<ref name=\"SW\"/> || ''[[SO