laim!]] |url= http://exclaim.ca/Reviews/DanceAndElectronic/laid_back-cosyland |accessdate= 25 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"OHW\">{{cite web|title= Like, Omigod! It's the '80s Pop Culture Box (Totally) |quote= There are also tracks to represent the rise of post-disco club/dance trend, such as Laid Back's \"White Horse\", New Edition's \"Cool It Now\", and Timex Social Club's \" Rumors\". |website= One Hit Wonder Center |accessdate= 29 October 2013 |url= http://www.onehitwondercenter.com/archive/reviews/review_popculturebox_80.htm}}</ref> || ''EMI Music Denmark''\n|-\n|Madonna || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[Burning Up (Madonna song)|Burning Up]]\"{{sfn|Brackett|Hoard|2004|p=508|ps=: That gift was there on her 1983 debut, which combined proven postdisco club tracks like \"Everybody\" and \"Burning Up\" with breakthrough pop hits \"Borderline\" and \"Lucky Star.\"}} || ''Sire'' / ''Warner Bros.''\n|-\n|[[Midnight Star]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"Wet My Whistle\"{{sfn|Shapiro|2006|p=271}} || ''SOLAR''\n|-\n|[[Mtume]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[Juicy Fruit (song)|Juicy Fruit]]\"<ref name=\"Vice\">{{cite magazine|first= Christopher |last= Metler |first2= Ali |last2= Love |title= Ali Love P.U.M.P.s Up the Volume, Vibes and Weirdness |magazine= [[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |date= 17 July 2014 |url= http://thump.vice.com/words/ali-love-pumps-up-the-volume-vibes-and-weirdness |archivedate= 17 December 2014 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141217044457/http://thump.vice.com/words/ali-love-pumps-up-the-volume-vibes-and-weirdness |url-status= dead}}</ref> || ''Epic''\n|-\n|[[The S.O.S. Band]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[Just Be Good to Me]]\"<ref>{{cite web|first= Mallory |last= O\u2019Donnell |title= The Singles Jukebox \u2013 Jam and Lewis |url= http://stylusmagazine.com/articles/the_singles_jukebox/jam-and-lewis.htm |website= Stylus Magazine |date= 21 April 2006 |accessdate= 25 October 2014}}</ref> || ''[[Tabu Records|Tabu]]''\n|-\n|[[Shannon (singer)|Shannon]] || {{flagico