ine)|Revolver]] |issue= 68 |issn= 1527-408X |quote= the post-disco classic \"Last Night a D.J. Saved My Life\" by early-'80s New York crew Indeep |url-status= dead |url= http://www.revolvermag.com/content/gorgoroth |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100210060533/http://www.revolvermag.com/content/gorgoroth |archivedate= 10 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first= Sal |last= Cinquemani |url= http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/mariah-carey-glitter |title= Mariah Carey \u2013 Glitter |website= Slant Magazine |date= 21 August 2001 |accessdate= 26 October 2014 |quote= A cover of Indeep's 1982 post-disco classic \"Last Night a DJ Saved My Life\" personifies Carey's ambition like no other song she's ever recorded}}</ref> || ''Sound of New York''\n|-\n|[[Inner Life]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"Moment of My Life\"<ref name=\"Salsoul\"/> || ''Salsoul''\n|-\n|[[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[Everybody (Madonna song)|Everybody]]\"{{sfn|Brackett|Hoard|2004|p=508|ps=: That gift was there on her 1983 debut, which combined proven postdisco club tracks like \"Everybody\" and \"Burning Up\" with breakthrough pop hits \"Borderline\" and \"Lucky Star.\"}} || ''Sire'' / ''Warner Bros.''\n|-\n|Melba Moore || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[Love's Comin' At Ya]]\"{{sfn|Shapiro|2006|p=278}}<ref>{{cite news|first= Paul |last= Lester |title= Leverage Models (No 1,314) |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/jul/23/new-band-leverage-models |newspaper= The Guardian |quote= That song, that example of post-disco electro-funk, we mused, is so October 1982 it's not true. |date= 23 July 2012 |accessdate= 17 December 2014}}</ref> || ''EMI America'' / ''Capitol''\n|-\n|[[Peech Boys]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || \"[[Don't Make Me Wait (Peech Boys song)|Don't Make Me Wait]]\" / \"Life Is Something Special\"<ref>{{cite book|title= Generation Ecstasy: Into the World of Techno and Rave Culture |first= Simon |last= Reynolds |authorlink= Simon Reynolds |url= https://books