y Jones <small>feat. [[Al B. Sure!]], James Ingram, [[El DeBarge]], [[Barry White]]</small>\n| Quincy Jones, [[Siedah Garrett]], El DeBarge\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|31\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|1\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|67\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 1991\n| \"Givin' In to Love\"\n| Patti Austin\n| \n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|-\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|55\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|-\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1993\n| \"Never Do You Wrong\"\n| [[Stephanie Mills]]\n| Vassal Benford, Ron Spearman, [[Carol Duboc]]\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|-\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|33\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|57\n| \n|-\n| \"Two in a Million\"\n| [[Mica Paris]]\n| \n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|-\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|-\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|51\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 1994\n| \"Vibe\" (includes a sample of \"Love X Love,\" from ''[[Give Me the Night (album)|Give Me the Night]]'', 1980)\n| [[Zhan\u00e9]]\n| Kier Gist, Ren\u00e9e Neufville\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|119\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|33\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|67\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1995\n| \"[[Hey Lover]]\" (includes a sample of \"The Lady in My Life,\" from ''[[Thriller (Michael Jackson album)|Thriller]]'', 1982)\n| [[LL Cool J]]\n| [[James Todd Smith]]\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|3\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|3\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|17\n| \n|-\n| \"[[You Put a Move on My Heart]]\"\n| [[Tamia]]\n| \n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|98\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|16\n|align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"9e99\"|-\n| First recorded by Mica Paris\n|-\n|}\n\n==Production credits==\n*the ''[[Running Scared (1986 film)|Running Scared]]'' soundtrack album, 1986 (with Dick Rudolph and Bruce Swedien)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/running-scared-1986-original-soundtrack-mw0000897681/credits|title=Running Scared [1986 Original Soundtrack] |publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=8 October 2016}}</ref>\n*\"We Belong to Love\" by [[Jeffrey Osborne]], from ''[[Emotional (Jeffrey Osborne album)|Emotional]]'', 1986<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/emotional-mw0000191326/credits|title=Emotional - Jeffrey Osborne |publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=8 October 2016}}</ref>\n*''[[Kiss of Life (Siedah Garrett album)|Kiss of Life]]'' by [[Siedah Garrett]], 1988 (with Dick Rudolph)<ref>{{cite web|title=Siedah Garrett  \u2013 Kiss Of Life|url=https://www.discogs.com/Siedah-Garrett-Kiss-Of-Life/release/1860628|website=Discogs|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref>\n*''[[Back on the Block]]'' by Quincy Jones, 1989 (associate producer)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Quincy-Jones-Back-On-The-Block/release/3399358|title=Quincy Jones - Back On The Block|publisher=discogs.com|accessdate=8 October 2016}}</ref>\n*\"Givin' In to Love\" by [[Patti Austin]], from ''Carry On'', 1991<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_bCgEAAAAMBAJ|title=Billboard: Single Reviews|date=12 October 1991|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|accessdate=7 October 2016|via=Internet Archive |page=[https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_bCgEAAAAMBAJ/page/n114 81]}}</ref>\n*\"You Put a Move on My Heart\", \"We Were Made for Love\", \"Two in a Million\", and \"Love Keeps Coming Back\" by [[Mica Paris]], from ''[[Whisper a Prayer]]'', 1993<ref>{{cite web|title=Mica Paris  \u2013 Whisper A Prayer|url=https://www.discogs.com/Mica-Paris-Whisper-A-Prayer/release/1785080|website=Discogs|accessdate=11 October 2016}}</ref>\n*\"We Are the Future\", from ''We Are the Future: You Are the Answer'', 2004 (with Sunny Levine)<ref>{{cite web|title=Various  \u2013 We Are The Future: You Are The Answer|url=https://www.discogs.com/Various-We-Are-The-Future-You-